Edition:
Quote:  The <i>kararahe</i> [a2,a3,e-acute], or dog (Canis Australis), which, when young, is known as <i>kuri</i>, has been an inhabitant some two or three centuries. <i>ibid.</i> 2/46 The native name is kuri, the general name for the dog amongst the Polynesian race; but it is very curious that the Spanish word `pero' is also known to them.
