Author:
Vol / Page:  55/153
Edition:
Quote:  <i>kuri</i>, Maori dog, brought with him from the Pacific; now applied to any mongrel: long extinct, and only surviving in the strips of skin with hair attached used as ornaments on the Maori valued cloaks (kaku-waero).
Notes:  Andersen Maori Words in English

